    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "act": "THE PI PULSE",
      "estimated_duration_s": 12,
      "narration_text": "A pi pulse about a transverse axis rotates every Bloch vector by one hundred eighty degrees. In the rotating-frame phase picture, plus phi maps to minus phi: the ordering of accumulated phases is reversed.",
